Emergency services in Johannesburg are on high alert as heavy rains are expected to continue. Johannesburg EMS spokesperson Nana Radebe-Kgiba spoke with eNCA's Jane Dutton. Courtesy of #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Emergency services in Johannesburg are on high alert as heavy rains are expected to continue. Residents in low-lying areas and motorists are urged to be extra cautious. READ: More heavy rain expected as tropical storm Eloise makes landfall Johannesburg EMS spokesperson Nana Radebe-Kgiba said there have not been reports of major incidents on the road and urged motorists to drive carefully to avoid trouble. "Make sure you keep a safe distance when driving and if there are any flooded roads, please avoid them. You cannot just calculate the water level with just your eyes," Radebe-Kgiba said.